{"title_page": "Third Roman cabinet (Romania)", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=June 2019|bot=noref (GreenC bot)}}\n{{Infobox government cabinet\n| cabinet_name            = Roman III\n| cabinet_number          = 109th\n| jurisdiction            = Romania\n| flag                    = Flag of Romania.svg\n| incumbent               = \n| image                   = Petre Roman.jpg\n| date_formed             = 30 April 1991\n| date_dissolved          = 16 October 1991\n| government_head         = [[Petre Roman]]\n| government_head_history =  \n| state_head              = [[Ion Iliescu]]\n| current_number          = \n| former_members_number   = \n| total_number            = \n| political_party         = [[National Salvation Front (Romania)|FSN]]\n| legislature_status      = Majority\n| opposition_cabinet      = \n| opposition_party        = \n| opposition_leader       = \n| election                = -\n| last_election           = -\n| legislature_term        = 1990 - 1992\n| budget                  = \n| incoming_formation      = \n| outgoing_formation      = \n| previous                = [[Roman II Cabinet|Roman II]]\n| successor               = [[Stolojan I Cabinet|Stolojan I]]\n}}\n\nThe cabinet of [[Prime Minister of Romania|prime minister]] of [[Romania]] [[Petre Roman]] from 30 April 1991 through 16 October 1991 was the third [[cabinet (government)|cabinet]] with him as prime minister.\n\n==Members==\n[[List of political parties in Romania|Coalition members]]: {{legend2|#cff|[[National Salvation Front (Romania)|FSN]]}}, and {{legend2|#d5d5d5|Independent ministers}}\n\n[[Prime Minister of Romania|Prime Minister]]: \n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Petre Roman]]</span>/<span style=\"background: #d5d5d5;\">[[Theodor Stolojan]]</span>(ad interim)\n\nMinister of State:\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Dan Mircea Popescu]]</span> (Co-ordinating Quality of Life)\n\nMinisters:\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Victor Babiuc]]</span> ([[Ministry of Justice (Romania)|Justice]])\n*<span style=\"background: #d5d5d5;\">[[Niculae Spiroiu]]</span> ([[Ministry of National Defense (Romania)|Defense]])\n*<span style=\"background: #d5d5d5;\">[[Andrei Ple\u0219u]]</span> ([[Ministry of Culture (Romania)|Culture and Arts]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Ioan \u021aipu]]</span> ([[Ministry of Agriculture, Forests and Rural Development (Romania)|Agriculture]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Adrian N\u0103stase]]</span> ([[List of Romanian Foreign Ministers|Foreign Affairs]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Eugen Dijm\u0103rescu]]</span> ([[Ministry of Economy and Commerce (Romania)|Economy]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Doru Viorel Ursu]]</span> ([[List of Romanian Ministers of the Interior|Interior]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Gheorghe \u0218tefan (Minister of Education)|Gheorghe \u0218tefan]]</span> ([[Ministry of Education and Research (Romania)|Education]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Valeriu Eugen Pop]]</span> ([[Ministry of Environment and Waters Management (Romania)|Environment]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Mihnea Marinache]]</span> ([[Ministry of Labor, Social Solidarity and Family (Romania)|Labor]])<ref>{{cite web|language=ro|url=https://jurnalul.antena3.ro/stiri/politica/dezgroparea-mortilor-126096.html|editor=Jurnalul Na\u021bional|title=Dezgroparea mor\u0163ilor|author=Gabriela Antoniu|date=3 June 2008|access-date=29 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|language=ro|author=Stan Stoica|page=291|title=Rom\u00e2nia dup\u0103 1989|year=2010|editor=Meronia|isbn=978-973-7839-33-6}}</ref>\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Traian B\u0103sescu]]</span> ([[Ministry of Transport, Constructions and Tourism (Romania)|Transport]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Bogdan Marinescu]]</span> ([[Ministry of Health (Romania)|Health]])\n*<span style=\"background: #cff;\">[[Andrei Chiric\u0103]]</span> ([[Ministry of Communications and Information Technology (Romania)|Commu