ard\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2016\n| [[Style Icon Asia#2016|8th Style Icon Asia]]\n| Awesome Swagger\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Herself\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Cable TV Awards\n| Cable Star Awards \u2013 Best Singer\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 15th [[KBS Entertainment Awards]]\n| Best Newcomer in Variety Show\n| {{nominated}}\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jessi}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:South Korean female rappers]]\n[[Category:South Korean female singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean hip hop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean television personalities]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in South Korea]]\n[[Category:American female rappers]]\n[[Category:American dance musicians]]\n[[Category:American television personalities]]\n[[Category:American musicians of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American people of South Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American women of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:Rappers from New York City]]\n[[Category:Unpretty Rapstar contestants]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American rappers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jessi\n| image              = Jessi (musician, 2016, cropped).jpg\n| caption            = Jessi at the December 2016 [[KBS Entertainment Awards]]\n| birth_name         = Jessica Hyun-ju Ho\n| alias              = Jessica H.O\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1988|12|17}}\n| birth_place        = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| education          = Korea Kent Foreign School\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*Singer-songwriter\n*Rapper\n}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n*[[K-pop]]\n*[[K-rap]]\n*[[hip hop music|hip hop]]\n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2005\u2013present\n| label           = {{flatlist|\n*[[YMC Entertainment|YMC]]\n*P-Nation\n}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n*[[Uptown (band)|Uptown]]\n*[[Lucky J]]\n*[[Sister's Slam Dunk]]}}\n}}\n| website            = \n| module2            = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| hangulstage    = {{linktext|\uc81c|\uc2dc}}\n| rrstage        = Jesi\n| mrstage        = Jeshi\n| hangul    = {{linktext|\ud638|\ud604|\uc8fc}}\n| hanja     = {{linktext|\u80e1|\u8ce2|\u73e0}}\n| rr        = Ho Hyeon-ju\n| mr        = Ho Hy\u014fn-ju\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Jessica Hyun-ju Ho''' (born December 17, 1988), better known by her stage name '''Jessi''', is a Korean-American rapper, singer, and songwriter based in South Korea. She was born in New York, raised in New Jersey, and moved to South Korea at the age of 15.<ref>After School Club (episode 178 featuring Jessi)</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2003\u20142014: Early career and Lucky J===\nIn 2003, Jessi successfully auditioned for Doremi Media and moved to South Korea at age 15.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaboo.com/video/the-10-year-journey-from-jessica-h-o-to-lucky-js-jessi/|title=The 10 Year Journey from Jessica H.O to Lucky J's Jessi|date=7 February 2015|publisher=}}</ref> She released her debut single album ''Get Up'' in 2005 and performed the title song \"Get Up\" on the TV series [[Music Bank (TV series)|''Music Bank'']]. In 2006 the hip hop group [[Uptown (band)|Uptown]] featured her in their album ''Testimony'', replacing their original vocalist [[Yoon Mi-rae]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/program/program_musicnews_frame.htm?No=4091&current_page=258|title=KBS World Radio K-POP News|website=world.kbs.co.kr}}</ref> Jessi's second single album, entitled \"The Rebirth\", was released in January 2009. After the release, she took a break from music, and left Korea to return to America.<ref name=\"interest1\">{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/88708/unprettyrapstar-jessi-interview|title=[Interview] \u2032Unpretty Rapstar\u2032 Jessi Spills on Why She Left Korea, Struggling with Korean Culture and More - Mwave|website=mwave.interest.me|access-date=2015-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160627185520/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/88708/unprettyrapstar-jessi-interview|archive-date=2016-06-27|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, after a 5-year hiatus, Jessi returned as a member of hip-hop trio [[Lucky J]] with rapper [[J'Kyun]] and vocalist J-Yo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2014/07/jessica-ho-to-start-anew-under-ymc-entertainments-upcoming-group-lucky-j|title=Jessica H.o. to start anew under YMC Entertainment's upcoming group Lucky J|publisher=}}</ref> Lucky J debuted with the digital single \"Can You Hear Me\" under [[Imagine Asia|YMC Entertainment]] in July of that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2014/07/co-ed-hip-hop-trio-lucky-j-kick-off-their-activities-with-can-you-hear-me-mv|title=Co-ed hip hop trio Lucky J kick off their activities with 'Can You Hear Me' MV|publisher=}}</ref> A month after their debut, Lucky J made an appearance in [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s music competition program, [[Immortal Songs: Singing the Legend|''Immortal Songs 2'']].\n\n===2015\u2014present: Television roles and P-Nation===\n\nFrom January to March 2015, Jessi was part of the first season of ''[[Unpretty Rapstar]]'', a spin-off of the program ''[[Show Me the Money (South Korean TV series)|Show Me The Money]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2015/01/11/mnet-to-launch-koreas-first-ever-female-rapper-survival-show-unpretty-rapstar/|title=Mnet to Launch Korea's First-Ever Female Rapper Survival Show \"Unpretty Rapstar\" - Soompi|website=www.soompi.com}}</ref> ''Unpretty Rapstar'' is a female rapper survival program, where contestants compete for the chance to be featured on tracks in a compilation album. Jessi was chosen as the second-place winner of the show by audience vote.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/03/and-the-winner-of-unpretty-rapstar-is/|title=And the winner of 'Unpretty Rapstar' is....?|publisher=}}</ref> After her appearance on ''Unpretty Rapstar'', Jessi was featured in [[Park Jin Young|JYP]]'s single \"Who's Your Mama?\" and its music video, which were both released in April 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6531820/jy-park-whos-your-mama-jessi-mv/|title=J.Y. Park Gives PSY a Run for His Money With Ode to Big Butts, 'Who's Your Mama?'|publisher=}}</ref> The track topped all nine major music charts in Korea as soon as it was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaboo.com/news/j-y-parks-whos-mama-tops-7-charts-first-place/|title=J.Y. Park's \"Who's Your Mama\" tops 7 charts in first place|date=15 April 2015|publisher=}}</ref> Throughout 2015, Jessi appeared as a guest in various popular variety shows, including [[Running Man (TV series)|''Running Man'']] and [[Happy Together (2001 TV series)|''Happy Together'']].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://program.sbs.co.kr/builder/endPage.do?pgm_id=00000330171&pgm_mnu_id=3413&bbsCd=&contNo=22000129675|title=\uc720\uc7ac\uc11d \"\uc81c\uc2dc, \uc30d\uaebc\ud480 \uc218\uc220 \uc804\uc774 \ud6e8\uc52c \uc608\ubed0\"|website=program.sbs.co.kr}}</ref><ref>[http://kbsworld.kbs.co.kr/programs/programs_intro.html?no=82 {KBS Happy Together} Suzy, Jessi, Seo Woo & more! (2015.04.23)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150524115143/http://kbsworld.kbs.co.kr/programs/programs_intro.html?no=82 |date=2015-05-24 }}</ref> She released her first ever solo rap single, \"Ssenunni\", on September 15.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.soompi.com/2015/09/01/jessi-to-make-a-hip-hop-comeback/|title=Jessi to Make a Hip Hop Comeback|publisher=soompi|accessdate= 2015-09-04}}</ref> Jessi's first live performance in the US was held on October 16. She performed at the Belasco Theater in [[Los Angeles]] with hip-hop duo [[Mighty Mouth]] as her opening act.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/09/go-see-unpretty-rapstars-jessi-at-the-belasco-theater-in-los-angeles-on-october-16th/|title=Go see Unpretty Rapstar's Jessi at the Belasco Theater in Los Angeles on October 16th!|publisher=}}</ref> When ''[[Unpretty Rapstar 2]]'' aired, Jessi appeared in several episodes as a mentor. She and [[Cheetah (rapper)|Cheetah]], the winner of the previous season, were featured in ''Unpretty Rapstar 2'' tracks produced by [[Verbal Jint]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2015/09/18/sparks-fly-between-jessi-and-kittib-on-unpretty-rapstar-2/|title=Sparks Fly Between Jessi and KittiB on \"Unpretty Rapstar 2\" - Soompi|website=www.soompi.com}}</ref> In December 2015, Jessi performed her song \"Ssenunni\" at the [[Mnet Asian Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://officiallykmusic.com/jessi-kills-it-at-2015-mamas-with-her-performance-of-ssenunni-video/|title=Jessi Kills It At 2015 MAMAs With Her Performance Of 'Ssenunni' [VIDEO] - The latest kpop news and music - Officially Kmusic|website=officiallykmusic.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Jessi starred as one of the permanent members in season 1 of popular Korean variety show, ''[[Sister's Slam Dunk]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title = Jessi, Tiffany, Min Hyo Rin, and more get together for a viewing party of their new variety show!|url =http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/04/jessi-tiffany-min-hyo-rin-and-more-get-together-for-a-viewing-party-of-their-new-variety-show|accessdate = 2017-07-10}}</ref> In 2017, Jessi released another rap single, \"Gucci\" from her first mini-album, entitled ''Un2verse'', both of which released on July 13.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/un2verse-ep/id1259130927|title=Un2verse - EP by Jessi|date=13 July 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kpopscene.com/jessi-un2verse-1st-mini-album/|title=Jessi \u2013 Un2verse - 1st Mini Album - KpopScene.com|website=KpopScene.com}}</ref> In 2018, Jessi starred on ''Yo! MTV Raps''. The show aired on MTV Asia on July 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtvasia.com/news/qa9zdp/meet-the-12-artists-in-the-spotlight-for-yo-mtv-raps-return|title=Meet the 12 artists in the spotlight for Yo! MTV Raps\u2019 return - MTV Asia|website=MTV Asia}}</ref> On the same day, she released a single titled \"Down\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8464307/jessi-down-music-video|title=Jessi Aims to Break South Korean Societal Norms & Gets 'Down' In New Music Video: Watch|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-08-26}}</ref> According to Soompi, [[AOMG]] producer [[Gray (singer)|Gray]] took part in producing the track.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/2018/06/30/july-comebacks-releases-coming-way/|title=July Comebacks And Releases Coming Your Way - Soompi|website=www.soompi.com}}</ref>\nHer contract with YMC Entertainment ended in October 2018, and in January 2019 she signed under PSY's record label P Nation.\n\n==Personal life==\nJessi attended Korea Kent Foreign School along with [[Girls' Generation]] members [[Tiffany Hwang|Tiffany]] and [[Jessica Jung]]. Former [[The Grace (band)|CSJH The Grace]] member and current solo singer [[Stephanie (South Korean singer)|Stephanie Kim]] also attended the same school. Jessi successfully passed an [[S.M. Entertainment]] audition, the same company her three classmates were all under. However, she chose not to become part of the label, as she believed its approach to music did not match her style.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/12/jessi-could-have-become-a-member-of-girls-generation|title=Jessi could have become a member of Girls' Generation?|publisher=}}</ref> Before Jessi went on temporary hiatus from the music industry, she struggled to become accustomed to Korean culture.<ref name=\"interest1\"/> She did not find immediate success after her debut, and was sometimes forced to sleep in [[saunas]] when she did not have enough money for a place to stay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2015/05/20/jessi-on-her-tough-unni-image-difficulties-after-debuting-and-not-paying-attention-to-haters/ |title=Jessi on Her \u2018Tough Unni\u2019 Image, Difficulties After Debuting, and Not Paying Attention to Haters |publisher=Soompi |date=2015-05-20 |accessdate=2018-07-18}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, during her break from the music industry, a controversy about Jessi's involvement in an alleged assault surfaced.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/06/jessica-ho-accused-of-assaulting-a-woman|title=Singer Jessica H.o. accused of assaulting a woman|publisher=}}</ref> The professed victim soon dropped the charges against the singer, and the investigation was closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/06/ms-choi-drops-charges-against-jessica-ho-for-alleged-assault|title=Ms. Choi drops charges against Jessica H.o. for the alleged assault|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:25em;\"| Details\n! colspan=\"1\" colspan=2\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Gaon Chart|KOR]]<br><ref>Peak chart positions for the following albums in South Korea:\n*''Un2verse'': {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?termGbn=week&hitYear=2017&targetTime=29&nationGbn=T|title=|script-title=ko:2017\ub144 29\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart|trans-title=Week 29 of 2017 Album Chart|website=Gaon Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|language=ko|access-date=July 26, 2017}}\n</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard charts|US<