{"title_page": "China\u2013Mongolia border", "text_new": "{{More references|date=July 2015}}\n{{Multiple image\n| image1 = Boundary marker of China.svg\n| image2 = Boundary marker of Mongolia.svg\n| width  = 50\n| footer = Chinese and Mongolian boundary markers\n}}\nThe border between China and Mongolia is the line that limits the territory of [[People's Republic of China]] and [[Mongolia]]; it stretches {{convert|4630|km|mi|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/mg.html|title=MONGOLIA|accessdate=31 January 2020|quote=China 4630 km}}</ref> from east to west and touches both the [[China\u2013Russia border]] and the [[Mongolia\u2013Russia border]].\n\nThe western end is located 55&nbsp;km from the beginning of the [[Kazakhstan\u2013Russia border]] and is marked by the [[Altai Mountains]] in [[Xinjiang]]. The eastern end of the border includes the [[Gobi Desert]] in [[Hulunbei'er]], formerly of [[Heilongjiang]].\n\n==China\u2013Mongolia border==\n{{See also|Sex trafficking in Mongolia|Sex trafficking in China}}\n\nMongolian and Chinese women and girls are sex trafficked to and through the China\u2013Mongolia border border.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2009-07-22/stolen-mongolia-sex|title=Stolen from Mongolia for sex|date=July 22, 2009|website=PRI}}</ref> At the border and in the [[Gobi Desert]] are global mining sector and other heavy industry operations with large workforces of isolated men. These, including the ones in [[Tavan Tolgoi|Tavan Tolgoi coal deposits]]  have been a focal point for prostitution and sex trafficking.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/global-health/women-and-girls/mongolias-prostitution-zones-women-trade-sex-fuel-sub-zero-temperatures/|title=Mongolia's prostitution zones, where women trade sex for fuel in sub-zero temperatures|date=February 19, 2019|website=The Telegraph}}</ref>\n\n==Historical maps==\nHistorical maps of the border from west to east from the [[International Map of the World]], middle 20th century (partial):\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"160\">\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nm-45-3rd-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nl-46-1st-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nk-46-3rd-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nk-47-1st-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nk-48-1st-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nk-49-2nd-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nl-49.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nm-50-3rd-ed.jpg|\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [https://fall.law.fsu.edu/collection/LimitsinSeas/IBS173.pdf International Boundary Study No. 173 \u2013 August 14, 1984 China \u2013 Mongolia Boundary]\n\n{{Borders of China}}\n{{Borders of Mongolia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mongolia-China border}}\n[[Category:China\u2013Mongolia relations|border]]\n[[Category:China\u2013Mongolia border| ]]\n[[Category:Borders of China]]\n[[Category:Borders of Mongolia]]\n[[Category:International borders]]\n\n\n{{Asia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More references|date=July 2015}}\n{{Multiple image\n| image1 = Boundary marker of China.svg\n| image2 = Boundary marker of Mongolia.svg\n| width  = 50\n| footer = Chinese and Mongolian boundary markers\n}}\nThe border between China and Mongolia is the line that limits the territory of [[People's Republic of China]] and [[Mongolia]]; it stretches {{convert|4630|km|mi|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/mg.html|title=MONGOLIA|accessdate=31 January 2020|quote=China 4630 km}}</ref> from east to west and touches both the [[China\u2013Russia border]] and the [[Mongolia\u2013Russia border]].\n\nThe western end is located 55&nbsp;km from the beginning of the [[Kazakhstan\u2013Russia border]] and is marked by the [[Altai Mountains]] in [[Xinjiang]]. The eastern end of the border includes the [[Gobi Desert]] in [[Hulunbei'er]], formerly of [[Heilongjiang]].\n\n==China\u2013Mongolia border==\n{{See also|Sex trafficking in Mongolia|Sex trafficking in China}}\n\nMongolian and Chinese women and girls are sex trafficked to and through the [[China\u2013Mongolia border]] border.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2009-07-22/stolen-mongolia-sex|title=Stolen from Mongolia for sex|date=July 22, 2009|website=PRI}}</ref> At the border and in the [[Gobi Desert]] are global mining sector and other heavy industry operations with large workforces of isolated men. These, including the ones in [[Tavan Tolgoi|Tavan Tolgoi coal deposits]]  have been a focal point for prostitution and sex trafficking.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/global-health/women-and-girls/mongolias-prostitution-zones-women-trade-sex-fuel-sub-zero-temperatures/|title=Mongolia's prostitution zones, where women trade sex for fuel in sub-zero temperatures|date=February 19, 2019|website=The Telegraph}}</ref>\n\n==Historical maps==\nHistorical maps of the border from west to east from the [[International Map of the World]], middle 20th century (partial):\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"160\">\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nm-45-3rd-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nl-46-1st-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nk-46-3rd-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nk-47-1st-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nk-48-1st-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nk-49-2nd-ed.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nl-49.jpg|\nFile:Txu-oclc-6654394-nm-50-3rd-ed.jpg|\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [https://fall.law.fsu.edu/collection/LimitsinSeas/IBS173.pdf International Boundary Study No. 173 \u2013 August 14, 1984 China \u2013 Mongolia Boundary]\n\n{{Borders of China}}\n{{Borders of Mongolia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mongolia-China border}}\n[[Category:China\u2013Mongolia relations|border]]\n[[Category:China\u2013Mongolia border| ]]\n[[Category:Borders of China]]\n[[Category:Borders of Mongolia]]\n[[Category:International borders]]\n\n\n{{Asia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wikipedianuhai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eChina\u2013Mongolia border", "url_page": 